"ElsaGate" (a primarily 2016 and 2017 shock video phenomenon) was a pivotal moment in YouTube history. 

When the YouTube Kids app became overrun with inappropriate content, purely for the sake of ad revenue, drastic changes were made to the website during a media and advertiser firestorm, but now (in 2025) there is a new wave of AI driven slop infesting keywords targetted at children, with a multitude of distinct similarities.

As the content spread like a virus, little to nothing is being done about it, by a platform that seems to be ignoring a problem rather than proactively solving it. ElsaGate 2.0 is on the cusp of being here.
